    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-03-22T17:15:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-03-22T17:15:00-05:00" n="238"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d238">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BC Indonesia/3–2249: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Representative at the United Nations</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Austin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret   urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-03-22T17:15:00-05:00"
                            >March 22, 1949—5:15 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>394. Following is text revised draft referred to mytel 393, March 22:</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“It is the sense of the <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> that <gloss
                            target="#t_UNCFIN1">UNCFI</gloss>, in accordance with the Council’s
                        resolution of 28 January and without prejudicing the rights, claims and
                        position of the parties, should assist the parties in reaching agreement as
                        to (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) the implementation of the Council’s resolution
                        of 28 January and in particular paragraphs 1 and 2 of the operative part
                        thereof, and (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) the time and conditions for holding
                        the proposed conference at The Hague, to the end that the negotiations
                        contemplated by the resolution of 28 January may be held as soon as
                        possible. It is further the sense of the Council that, if such an agreement
                        is reached, the holding of such a conference and the participation by <gloss
                            target="#t_UNCFIN1">UNCFI</gloss> in accordance with its terms of
                        reference would be consistent with the purposes and objectives of the
                        Council’s resolution of 28 January, 1949.”</p>
                </quote>
                <p>Please relay Batavia for Cochran.<note n="1" xml:id="d238fn1">This was done the
                        same day.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Austin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
